dct_title_s: The Congo River, from its mouth to Bolobo to illustrate the journeys of Mr. H. H. Johnston
dct_description_sm: Rapids and falls are shown. Conjectural courses of rivers and lakes shown by broken lines. Relief shown by hachures and spot heights. From: Proceedings of the Royal Geographical Society and monthly record of geography. Vol. 5 (1885), no. 10, pp. 569-81; held in Firestone Library. Call number: G7 .J6873
